<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-22T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-22T23:00:00-05:00" n="513" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d513">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9588: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-23T13:00:00+09:00">August 23, 1937—1
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 23—1:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>297. Department’s No. 159, August 21, 11 p.m., Tsingtao. Department’s
                                instructions received this morning were carried out in a formal note
                                to the Minister for Foreign Affairs which I delivered to <pb facs="0465" n="458" xml:id="pg_458"/> the Vice Minister shortly
                                after noon. No alterations were made in the Department’s text. The
                                Vice Minister made no comment except to say that the matter would be
                                studied.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>